Nope.  This isn't valid.  We don't have a HOST 0.  If there is some magic enabled by this, we need to handle that somehow separately than just changing HOST_INSTANCES because we're likely to break something else or have to un-magic it elsewhere (for example, how many ipmb channels do we launch?).

Hi Patrick,
I know this is not make sense but we found there is one to one structure between CHASSIS and HOST in meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/state/phosphor-state-manager-systemd-links.inc.

Could we separate chassis and host target in phosphor-state-manager-systemd-links.inc to change the one to one structure? This may be more flexible for multi host

Revised by removing HOST 0 and separing chassis and host target.
Thank you for your suggestion.

Warm-reboot is already enabled by default.  If we need this to be selectable it should go into the meta-phosphor recipe as a PACKAGECONFIG.

Don't ever change CFLAGS directly in a recipe.  Use meson_options.
I'll check it, thank you for your reviewing

The origin file will also be changed for multi-host target management, not for specific project only.
